<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 25 at 8:49PM PST  by NWS Portland</headline>
<description>...ICY ROADS BECOMING LIKELY TONIGHT...
Falling temperatures are allowing roads to cool quickly, even if
snow has yet to start. Take caution especially driving over
bridges and overpasses as black ice will form quicker on those
elevated colder surfaces. Additionally, snow falling on top of
this ice may make traction even more difficult.</description>
